## Conversation
Follow-on from the ts-v2 decouple stack review. User asked why message
templating / validation utils must live in weave/shared and whether they can be
broken out, then proposed contract tests asserting "the same shape on both
sides" because the impl can't be shared across languages (TypeScript). We
converged on a language-neutral golden corpus: a JSONL of (input -> expected)
examples that every SDK reimplements ser/de against. User confirmed: "the TS SDK
will need to write ser/de to match python. That is OK and expected"; skip PIL
(no PIL in TS, a client detail); "proceed with your work. Make it stack on top
of the existing PRs." This is PR7 of the stack (andrew/ts-v2-conformance-corpus
on top of andrew/ts-v2-server-worker-shared).

